Read AGENTS.md first — it is the canonical contract.
Use .ai/BOOTSTRAP.md and `npm run knowledge:context -- --task="..."` to resolve task context.
Never bypass architecture, package ownership, hook isolation, strict typing, tests, security,
accessibility, localization, or native safety. When a guardrail blocks you, move the code to the
correct layer instead of disabling the rule. Suppressions require a documented EXC-nnnn exception.
Do not edit generated .ai files: update canonical knowledge, then run `npm run knowledge:build`.
Every CI gate must be green before you commit and before you push — format, lint, typecheck,
contract, coverage/per-file, build, architecture and ownership checks, static analysis, e2e, a11y,
visual, security, knowledge build+validate, Capacitor sync, Android, iOS, and `all-gates-green`.
Fix the root cause; never weaken a rule, threshold, or coverage floor to make a gate pass. Rebuild
`.ai` with `npm run knowledge:build` and commit it with any src or corpus change.
UI/UX Quality Mandate: every UI must be cool, clear, vibrant, catchy and UX-perfect on web and
mobile — responsive (desktop sidebar+navbar, mobile tab bar+drawer), polished loaders and skeletons
for all async states, first-class dark + light mode, perfect RTL + LTR, accessible (WCAG AA), refined
components and tasteful motion. Plain/default styling is not acceptable.
